>Disadvantages</i><blockquote>\n<li>You have very little control over modified versions of your shortcut.</li>\n<li>Users have to install more shortcuts.</li>\n</blockquote></li><br><br>\n<h5>Why you should use VerifyKit</h5>\n<blockquote>\n<li>You have all the advantages of Separate Shortcuts</li>\n<li>You can be confident that your shortcut dependencies are unmodified</li>\n<li>You might even be able to block unofficial clones of your dependencies</li>\n<li>Your users will even be able to (at your discretion) verify shortcuts while offline!</li>\n</blockquote><br>\n<h6>Possible Disadvantages</h6>\n<blockquote>\n<li>VerifyKit <b>does not work</b> on shortcuts with import questions.</li>\n<li>VerifyKit is only for iOS 14.</li>\n<li>Your users still have to install more shortcuts.</li>\n<li>There is a possibility of the RoutineHub API being weird and throwing an error.</li>\n<li>Offline verification is mildly error-prone.</li>\n<li>VerifyKit only works for RoutineHub.</li>\n</blockquote><br><br>\n<h4>This all sounds amazing. How do I add VerifyKit?</h4>\n<p>You may manually copy the actions into your shortcut, or use some other method. I recommend <a href=\"https://routinehub.co/shortcut/4118/\">Copy And Paste A Shortcut</a> by <a href=\"https://routinehub.co/user/robric18\">@robric18</a>. To add VerifyKit into your shortcut, the \"Quick Copy\" option is best, as you should copy all actions into your shortcut.</p><br>\n<h3>Credits</h3>\n<blockquote>\n<li>Made and Published by: <b>OIRNOIR</b></li><br>\n<li>CryptoKit by <b>u/schl3ck</b></li>\n<li>MediaKit for this page by <b>ROP</b></li>\nSpecial thanks to:\n<li><b>mvan231</b> <i>(For showing me how to get a plist from an iCloud link, and also how to get the iCloud link from the RoutineHub API)</i></li>\n<li><b>FifiTheBulldog</b> <i>(For sharing much knowledge involving conversion between plist and json)</i></li>\n<li><b>Harley Hicks</b> <i>(Thanks for RoutineHub)</i></li>\n<li><b>zachary7829</b> <i>(Thanks for the ins